# Singapore Portal = Single Source of Truth

Reference: https://www.laduree.sg

When implementing any page, always inspect the corresponding page on laduree.sg first.

- Do not approximate
- Do not simplify
- Do not redesign

If information cannot be verified from the Singapore portal, stop and ask for approval. Do not invent content.

## What may differ from Singapore

Only these items may differ:

- Outlet name
- Outlet code
- Address
- Opening hours
- Last order time
- Product availability
- Thailand pricing
- Currency (THB)
- Payment methods
- Legal information

Everything else should match Singapore.

## Parity scope

Reproduce Singapore as closely as technically possible: IA, nav, menu hierarchy, page sequence, system wording, button/category labels, pickup workflow, cart/checkout, typography, colors, spacing, borders, component behavior, and mobile behavior.

## Never write customer-facing marketing copy

Never create any of the following unless they already exist in the Singapore portal or are explicitly provided by the project owner:

- headlines
- taglines
- descriptions
- promotional copy
- button wording
- section titles

Also do not invent: menu labels, category names, process names, or extra homepage sections.

Forbidden examples (unless exact Singapore wording or owner-approved):
- Luxury French Pâtisserie
- Luxury Pickup Experience
- Browse Collection
- Select Boutique

Reproduce Singapore terms exactly (e.g. Home, Menu, Recommended, About Us, Pick-up, Delivery, Select service, date and time, Pickup Time, Item(s) Added, Clear items, Checkout, All Items, Macaron Gift Boxes, ADD, View Cart, Allergen Information).

## Thailand data

See `.cursor/rules/thailand-localization.mdc` for the allowed differ list, THB formatting, and locale defaults.

## Content source rule

Customer-facing text must come from: (1) approved Singapore portal wording, (2) approved France/global brand material, or (3) Thailand ops info from the project owner (only for the allowed differ list above).

If none exists: stop and ask for approval — or use `[CONTENT PENDING APPROVAL]` only when the owner has directed that placeholder. Never invent replacement copy.
